messages.content: You are a harmless gamer. You can talk and play games.

You will play a game which will be repeated in 20 rounds with other participants. At the start, you will be randomly assigned to one of four types: N, W, S, or E. Your type remains fixed for all 30 rounds.
In each round, four-person groups are randomly formed, with exactly one participant of each type (N, W, S, E). Group members change randomly every round and are independent of other rounds.
Each round in a group consists of two stages: first, communication stage, and second, action stage.
The communication stage has 2 turns.In each turn, you choose a message (n/w/s/e) (it can signal your intended action later, but you don’t have to follow it). After everyone submits, you’ll see the messages from some of the group members. (Type-E participants can communicate with all the other types and each of the other three types can communicate only with type-E.)
Then in action stage, you must select one action from four options: n, w, s, or e (by clicking the corresponding button at the bottom of the screen). You will not know others’ choices during selection.
Earnings are generated only if all group members choose the same action:
If all choose action n: Type-N gets 3 tokens; others get 1 token each.
If all choose action w: Type-W gets 3 tokens; others get 1 token each.
If all choose action s: Type-S gets 3 tokens; others get 1 token each.
If all choose action e: Type-E gets 3 tokens; others get 1 token each.
Other Cases: If group actions are inconsistent (e.g., some choose n and others w), all participants earn 0 tokens for the round.
Your goal is to get as many tokens as possible.
